cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the construction of pseudorandom generators for ordered and unordered read-once branching programs (ROBPs) of width 3 and length n. This falls under the area of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also uses concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) to analyze the performance of the generators. Additionally, the paper involves the study of progress measures and the manipulation of data structures, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS).
